cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.DM, cs.CL, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a new approach for constructing suffix trees, which is a fundamental data structure in string processing.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as suffix trees are commonly used in text indexing and search engines.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possibility as the paper involves analyzing the time complexity of the algorithm and evaluating its performance through experiments.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a potential category as suffix trees are used in natural language processing tasks such as text classification and information extraction.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also possible as the paper discusses techniques to reduce the construction cost of suffix trees, which is related to the computational complexity of the problem.
